snippet.textDisplay:
I fell off my couch when Carlton got down on one knee. I really thought he was going to propose again. Seriously, this scene was so uncomfortable to watch. I felt for Diamond, she was in a no win situation.
Also, does anyone here wonder if Lauren could have had a successful relationship with any of the other guys? She and Damian talked everyday until the end, I can't see them as a couple though. I can see her with Kenny, they are both laid back and Kenny seems to be a good guy. Interestingly enough, Barnette was also someone that Lauren spoke with frequently, can you see that being a match? Lauren and Cameron both insinuated that they chose each other early on, so I don't think any of the other guys had a chance. I am curious as to why they still had to date others after they confessed their love to one another. Netflix hoping for drama?
